javax.servlet.sip

Interface SipWebSocketContext


  • public interface SipWebSocketContext
    Each SIP WebSocket connection established to a SIP Servlet container has an associated instance of SipWebSocketContext interface. Application may access this object either from SipServletMessage or from SipServletContext.
    Since:
    2.0
    See Also:
    SipServletMessage.getLocalSipWebSocketContext(), SipServletContext.getSipWebSocketContext(String)

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Flow getFlow()
      Returns the Flow of the SIP WebSocket connection.
      String getHttpHeader(String header)
      Returns the http header saved by the sip container at the time of websocket handshake.
      String getURL()
      Returns the fully qualified http URL used to complete the SIP WebSocket handshake.
      Principal getWebSecurityPrincipal()
      Returns a java.security.Principal object containing the name of the authenticated user at the time of websocket handshake.

        Returns the fully qualified http URL used to complete the SIP WebSocket handshake.

      • getFlow

        Flow getFlow()
        Returns the Flow of the SIP WebSocket connection. A Flow represents the transport association between the UA and the server.
        Returns:
        the Flow of the SIP WebSocket connection.

      • getWebSecurityPrincipal

        Principal getWebSecurityPrincipal()
        Returns a java.security.Principal object containing the name of the authenticated user at the time of websocket handshake.
        Returns:
        a java.security.Principal containing the name of the web user; null if the user has not been authenticated.

      • getHttpHeader

        String getHttpHeader(String header)
        Returns the http header saved by the sip container at the time of websocket handshake. A sip container that support sip over websockets is required to allow administrators to configure the names of http headers that will be saved.
        Returns:
        a serializable information object created by the application.
